sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the execution of programs as Launch Agents or Launch Daemons using launchctl on macOS.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a dropper that establishes persistence. It daemonizes itself, creates a LaunchAgent plist in `~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.<user>.hprtegdysfovlnga.plist`, and drops an AppleScript payload to `~/Library/hprtegdysfovlnga`. The LaunchAgent is then loaded via `launchctl` to execute the script, which fetches a C2 domain by scraping a Telegram channel page (`t.me/phefuckxiabot`). The binary also executes `killall Terminal` to hide its initial execution.
